translated: Hallberg, Sölve Odof Omskar, licensed physician, works physician. Born on January 8th, 1898 in Styrnäs, Västernorrland. Son of wholesale merchant Fritz H. and Hulda Strindlund. Married to Vera Blomdahl in 1926. Children: Elisabeth (Lisbeth) born in 1928 and Olof (Olle) born in 1931. Studied and received an exam in Härnösand in 1917, earned a degree in medicine at Uppsala University in 1923, and earned a medical license in Stockholm in 1927. Worked as an assistant physician at Svegs hospital in 1926, a bath doctor at Södertälje bath and spa in 1931, assistant and deputy physician at military hospitals in Sollefteå in 1935 and at Norrlands trängkår the same year, appointed as a railway doctor, medical physician at Härnösands hospital, and second physician at Gådeå hospital in 1936, and a provisional physician. He was also a community doctor in Högsjö, Västernorrland, a works physician in Olifstrom since 1937, and completed service at Boden's military hospital in 1941. He was also vice chairman of the Olofstrom's health committee and a member of its temperance and child welfare committees.
